# Git Workflow

Never commit automatically.

Never push automatically.

Never create releases automatically.

The developer always reviews every change before committing.

## File Changes

Only modify files required for the current task.

Avoid unnecessary formatting-only changes.

Do not rename files unless required.

## Pull Requests

Keep changes focused.

Avoid mixing multiple unrelated features into one implementation.

## Development Process

Every task should follow this workflow:

1. Understand the task.
2. Implement only the requested functionality.
3. Ensure the project builds successfully.
4. Explain what changed.
5. Stop and wait for developer review.